parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Footwell Control Module Corrosion)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the fuse in the footwell control module can cause various electrical system failures, including window malfunctions, warning light illuminations, and headlight failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Windows fail to open
unknown warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel
headlights fail to illuminate
turn signals fail to engage
interior lights fail to turn off
battery drains
exterior lights flash uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the vehicle to stall or disable while moving, leading to accidents or hazardous situations.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or disables while moving
ignition coil failure
fuse blows
electronic control unit failure
vehicle becomes inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in resolving the footwell control module recall can lead to frustration and inconvenience for vehicle owners, potentially affecting their trust in the manufacturer and the safety of their vehicle.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are informed about the recall
but the fix is not available
leading to repeated visits to the dealership without a resolution.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Overheating and Failure due to Faulty Temperature Housing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the temperature housing part can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle stalls on a busy highway.
symptoms: The temperature gauge warning light appears on the dashboard
followed by steam coming from the engine compartment
and the engine shutting off. The vehicle may not restart
and the engine may require replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty footwell module can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including backup lights, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: Inoperable backup lights
no warning lights illuminated
possible issues with other electrical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle stalls or dies
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage, or failure, which can result in costly repairs or even engine replacement.
symptoms: Oil spots or stains under the vehicle
oil drips or leaks from the engine
the oil level drops rapidly
the engine overheats
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations
the check engine light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure or malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels too far or too little
the brakes make unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause various vehicle systems to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle's lights
wipers
or other accessories malfunction
the vehicle's battery drains rapidly
the vehicle's electrical systems fail or malfunction
the vehicle's warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Brake Pedal Hardness and Loss of Braking Function
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden hardness of the brake pedal and loss of braking function can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at higher speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes extremely hard
making it difficult or impossible to slow down or stop the vehicle
the brake pedal does not respond to pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down using the brake pedal.
